    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Butler</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 2, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received January 8.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 103.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Upon receipt of your dispatch No. 131, of
                            December 13, 1895, regarding the extradition of Chester W. Rowe, I
                            submitted a copy of same, as also a copy of Mr. Lacey’s memorandum, to
                            Minister Mariscal, bespeaking his careful consideration of the views and
                            of the request of our Government therein contained.</p>
                <p>Inclosing copy of this legation’s note to Mr. Mariscal, I am, sir,
                            etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. C. Butler.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 103.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Butler</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Mariscal</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-31">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1895</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: I have the honor to submit copy
                                of a dispatch just received by this legation from the Department of
                                State, in regard to the case of Chester W. Rowe.</p>
                    <p>Bespeaking your excellency’s careful consideration of the views and
                                of the request of my Government, as contained therein, it honors me
                                to reiterate, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">E. C. Butler.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
